       Seleucus 
He did not order the ipparchy of the partners, so they appeared;
for this is Hephaestio first and foremost,
but after this Perdiccas, the third, the predestined
 Seleucus.

       tu, allora, 
Come vi abbiamo scritto prima, ascoltate questo;
poiché non permettiamo loro di fare ciò che è scritto."

       you, then, 
As we wrote to you before, you listen to this;
for we do not allow them to do what is written."

       but in this way you ordered the camp to descend
on the wars, you have perverted the order;
for the right horn, which indeed he believed, was projected,

The second one was sent, checked by me
to flee, not to compete.

       Diciotto viaggiatori di un giorno
e dopo tremila stadi si accamparono
sull'Automala;
c'era una montagna su entrambi i lati del pendio,
nel mezzo c'era una profonda gola, dalla quale sorgeva
pietra liscia a destra dello skopeleon ascendente;

       Eighteen day travelers
and after three thousand stadia they encamped
about Automala;
there was a mountain on both sides of the slope,
in the middle of it there was a deep gorge, from which it rose
smooth stone to right rising skopeleon;

ὅτι δὲ κατὰ τὴν Λιβύην γέγονεν αὕτη καὶ τὸν Εὐριπίδην δείξαι τις ἂν μαρτυροῦντα· λέγει γὰρ
τίς τοὔνομα τὸ ἐπονείδιστον βροτοῖς
οὐκ οἶδε Λαμίας τῆς Λιβυστικῆς γένος;

       Ordinò che Leptino fosse tentato
sfidare l'uomo alla battaglia;
prevalere come forza ribelle e sconfitta.

       He ordered that Leptinus be tempted
challenge the man to battle;
prevail as a rebel force and a vanquished one.

       but these had coverings for
machine protection, through which they received insurance
towards the roofs about the release of the arrows turning back;
for they were surrounded by fountains,
but full of anger, in the plague of the stone-throwers.
